FIRE DRAGON: Ancient supernatural MDC powerhouse

Young Fire Dragons are among the most powerful playable races in
AetherMUD.  They are ancient supernatural beings of enormous physical
capability, innate magic, psionic ability, and an MDC body that shrugs
off most conventional weapons.  Playing a dragon is a significant
commitment: they cannot enter most buildings, their needs are vast,
and they are hunted by nearly every faction on Rifts Earth.

ATTRIBUTES (APPROXIMATE RANGES)
  IQ: 15-30  ME: 13-28  MA: 11-26  PS: 25-50 (Supernatural)
  PP: 9-24   PE: 24-44  PB: 6-21   Spd: 14-34

DAMAGE POOL
  MDC: 4d6 x10 + 60 (approx 100-300 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6 (inner life force)

SPECIAL ABILITIES
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Fire breath weapon
  - Complete immunity to fire and heat
  - Natural flight
  - Nightvision 300 ft
  - Telemechanics: instinctively understand any machine
  - Sense Rifts and ley lines
  - Starting PPE: approximately 200+ (enormous magical reserve)

PENALTIES
  - Not OCC eligible, dragon nature defines the path
  - Dragon-sized: cannot enter most human-scale buildings
  - Hunted by Coalition, Gargoyle Empire, and dragon hunters
  - Conspicuous in any urban setting
  - Cannot use standard equipment

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any (dragons tend toward extreme alignments).

